e month of May, such as owing a feudal obligation then. In England, this name was possibly also a pet form of <i>Mary</i> or <i>Margaret</i>. This surname is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine) and Denmark.","English: nickname from Middle English <i>mey</i>, <i>may</i> ‘kinsman’."]}]},{"name":"Beatrice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["and French form of   Beatrix  , which was quite popular in England during the Middle Ages, and strongly revived in the 19th century. It is most famous as the name of Dante's beloved, and is borne by the elder (  b. 1988 ) of the Duke of York's daughters."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Beatrice Mayson was born in 1335, in Moulton, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Sir Richard de Welby before 1354, in Moulton, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1387, in her hometown, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1335–1387":"1335–1387","1340–1387":"1340–1387","1355–1410":"1355–1410","1335":"1335","before 1354":"enne 1354","1355":"1355","1410":"1410","1387":"1387","1340":"1340","Moulton, Lincolnshire, England":"Moulton, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Moulton, , Lincolnshire, England":"Moulton, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1335–1387":"1335–1387","1340–1387":"1340–1387","1355–1410":"1355–1410","1335":"1335","before 1354":"ennen vuotta 1354","1355":"1355","1410":"1410","1387":"1387","1340":"1340","Moulton, Lincolnshire, England":"Moulton, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Moulton, , Lincolnshire, England":"Moulton, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1335–1387":"1335–1387","1340–1387":"1340–1387","1355–1410":"1355–1410","1335":"1335","before 1354":"avant 1354","1355":"1355","1410":"1410","1387":"1387","1340":"1340","Moulton, Lincolnshire, England":"Moulton, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Moulton, , Lincolnshire, E